    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-08T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-08T17:00:00-05:00" n="401"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2373</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-08T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 8, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Department has received telegram signed by <persName>Lavrov</persName>,
                    President of the Council of Ministers, and <persName corresp="#p_DP1"
                        >Derber</persName>, Minister for Foreign Affairs, purporting to represent
                    the provisional government of autonomous Siberia and asking that any action
                    conducted in Siberia should have exclusive regard for the authorities of the
                    supreme power in Siberia represented by the aforesaid provisional
                        government.<note n="1" xml:id="d401fn1">Not printed.</note> For the
                    information of yourself and <persName corresp="#p_KAAM1">Admiral
                        Knight</persName>, the Department has not acknowledged this telegram and is
                    not prepared at this time to represent [recognize] any group or faction in
                    Siberia. In this same connection referring to a telegram from <persName
                        corresp="#p_KAAM1">Admiral Knight</persName> to the Navy Department, 21004,
                    and in view of the attitude of this Government just described, the Department
                    regards the presence of <persName corresp="#p_HGDL1">General Horvat</persName>
                    at Vladivostok as an embarrassment rather than an asset.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
